==English==

===Etymology===
* From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|academicien|académicien|lang=fr}}, from {{term|academie|académie||academy|lang=fr}}
* {{suffix|academic|ian|t2=one skilled in}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˌkæ.dəˈmɪ.ʃn̩/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌæk.ə.dəˈmɪ.ʃn̩/|/əˌkæ.dəˈmɪ.ʃn̩/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A member or follower of an [[academy]], or society for [[promoting]] science, art, or literature, as of the [[French Academy]], or the Royal Academy of Arts. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18th century.}}<ref name=SOED>Brown, Lesley, ed. ''The Shorter Oxford English Dictionary.'' 5th. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2003.</ref>
# A member of the faculty, or a student of a [[college]] or [[university]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18th century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# A believer of the traditional in philosophy, art, or literature.

